Great rising Kings and Warriors. This is so deep and needed. Not to create division but to honor our first true loves; our black queens.

A man’s first love is his mother. She is the Queen who nurtures and trains him as to who and what a Queen is. She demands respect, attention, affection, and even protection. Her example is the first example a son will know, so she must exemplify extraordinary strength, perseverance, loyalty, faithfulness, integrity, intelligence, elegance, self-esteem and a heir second to none. I am proud to say that I was blessed with such a Queen. Her essence and  majesty reign in my heart and soul and remains in the front of my mind at all times. My mother gave it all, so that I may have it all. I am a proud son and she should know that she did her job to the fullest. I respect women to the fullest and love them beyond measure. I am strong, deeply rooted in Spirit, confident, full of integrity and relentlessly ambitious. I have never beat, cursed or dogged a sister. I don’t father a bunch of children. (Actually I have none... guess im a late bloomer. SMH. Lol) I love my family, friends and life. All because you loved me! So I Thank YOU QUEEN!

#celgales #iprayweallmakeit

Great rising Kings and Queens and Warriors. In recognition of women appreciation month just a Message to my fellow Kings:

Be a healer! That’s what she truly needs! Enough men have sought to destroy her. Be the one to build her up, make her believe, give her assurance. Then you will see her true essence, beauty and power unveiled. You will notice that all the walls and barriers,once there as protection to keep you at bay, will begin to soften and eventually crumble. This is when you will benefit as a King. Because you have helped to affirm her identify as Queen, you will discover that there is great strength and majesty in the upliftment of one another mentally, physically & SPIRITUALLY, thus building an impenetrable bond that will give birth to endless possibilities. 

I’m no doctor, nor a professor. I have no alphabet to add to my name. I am however, in the know of who and what she is to the universe, to our communities, and to the survival of our existence.  I am in love with our sisters because, without them (grandmas, mothers, aunties, lovers, friends, girlfriends and wives alike) there is no you nor me!” -Cel (Grindit2ufindit) Gales
